What did you learn this year??
•
Every hour, day, week that goes by we are learning - whether we want to or not. It is how our brains work - They are sponges that are picking up the feedback, experiences, and interactions of our lives.
•
However, it is rare that we notice these “absorptions” as they happen.
•
But hindsight is always 20/20 - we can see very clearly (as we reflect retrospectively) what we have learned…
•
…And this is perhaps the greatest value of taking the time at milestones like the New Year, birthdays, anniversaries etc, to really ask yourself in full honesty and vulnerability…
•
“What have I learned? And am I where I want to be right now in my journey?”
•
Then answer yourself IN WRITING, and take MASSIVE ACTION to work towards what you want.
•
So….what did you learn??
•
•
•
#alwayslearningalwaysgrowing #thinkingminds #massiveaction #journalprompts #writeitdown #aĺwayslearning #reflectionstories #hindsightis2020 #retrospective #thejourneycontinues #lifelibertyandthepursuitofhappiness #readbooks #journalentry

“Baby It Ain’t Over (Til It’s Over)”..
•
Who remembers this early hit by @lennykravitz - SUCH a good song!!
•
I’ve always felt that it has such depth and meaning to life, and it’s struggles, that go far beyond the surface meaning of the song.
•
To me, it speaks to the dedication of human resolve and never-give-up attitude of anything. Relationships. Endeavors. Goal accomplishment. Success. Resilience.
•
Ultimately, NOTHING is “Over” until we deem it to be! It is our own IRON WILL that makes things succeed…
•
And it’s only when we CHOOSE to stop trying, or in some cases wasting our time, does something TRULY meet its demise.
•
I say… that makes us all very powerful in our lives.
•
I say…it makes us Masters of The Universe!
•
“Cuz baby it ain’t over til it’s over….”
•
•
•
#babyitaintovertillitsover #sundaysoul #sundayschool #nevergiveuponyourdreams #knockeddown7getup8 #keeppunching #onefootinfrontoftheother #notimetowaste #takecareofyourself

Obsession. My hope for everyone, is that at least ONCE in your life you find yourself in absolute obsession over achieving some goal.
•
The value of discipline, obsession, intensity, focus, and pragmatism are ALL highly discounted by the “experts” that want you to listen to them, buy their program, or go to their ass-clown “mastermind”.
•
The REAL TRUTH is that people that are inventing, revolutionizing, and keep their minds occupied in these traits listed above, don’t NEED to have someone else convince them that they can do something. You won’t meet them at a mastermind. You won’t see them at your “mixer”.
•
Stay DISCIPLINED. FOCUSED. PASSIONATE. VIGILANT. And OBSESSED with achieving your goals in all aspects of life, career, and health.
•
•
•
#allinchallenge #obsession #disciplineequalsfreedom

RE-Birthday!!!
•
19 years ago tonight, Oct 4, 2004, I died 3 times in one night.
•
I wish I could say that I HAD something to do with it… but I was completely incapacitated. Even my WILL was out of my own hands.
•
For many reasons, I am grateful.
•
My life.
•
My friends.
•
My opportunities.
•
My successes.
•
But MOST of all, I am grateful for my failures. After dying 3 times in one night, there is nothing that scares me.
•
Also… without my SCA’s, I never would have found the late legend Lucky Dog.
•
Hug your people. Shoot your shot. Say I love you a lot. Make it weird! You never know when it’s going to be the last day….and one day it will be.
•
•
•
#loveyourlifeorchangeit #survivorlife #resilient #neverquitever #iloveyouquotes #servicedogs #plotthoundoftheday
